# Markdown styleguide (repository prose)

## Scope (this repository only)

Applies when you add or revise narrative prose in tracked Markdown here (for example `README.md`, `notes/**/*.md`, `SemiformalProof/**/*.md`). It does not govern LaTeX in other trees unless those files are Markdown.

## Shared emphasis norms (keep in sync)

The following block is copied verbatim in `chapman-alignment-faking/.cursor/rules/styleguide.mdc`. **Change both files** when you revise these norms.

In narrative prose:

- Use Markdown `**bold**` sparingly. As a rule of thumb, **at most one bold span per sentence** (often zero is better).
- Prefer structure from headings, lists, and backticks for paths, commands, and identifiers instead of bold emphasis.
- Do not bold every list label or every proper noun unless emphasis is genuinely needed for the reader.

Exception: short machine-oriented glossaries (e.g. rigid field–value patterns) may keep bold labels for scanability; still avoid stacking multiple bold phrases in one sentence when you can rephrase.

## Semiformalizing-lattices only (do not merge into the shared block)

- **Italic used for stress** counts toward the same “one emphasised span per sentence” cap as bold (pick one or neither per sentence).
- **Contrast / takeaway** (guidance, not a second rule): use bold only when it marks a contrast the reader could miss, or a single takeaway line—not to dress up every noun or every bullet label. This does not relax the per-sentence cap above.
- **Policy tiering** for semiformal chapters lives in `notes/semiformal-proof-policy.md` (human `*.md`, assistant `*-ai.md`, bridge `*-bridge.md`); that file is orthogonal to this styleguide.
- **Semiformal proof labels** in `SemiformalProof/**`: human `*.md` uses `*Proof (human):*`; `-ai.md` uses `*Proof (human):*`, `*Proof (semiformalized from lean):*`, or `*Proof (human–ai–lean collaboration):*` only (see policy *Proof labels (provenance)*).
- **Semiformal sections** (policy *Semiformal section layout*): human uses title + id bold lines, optional `*Remark:*`, `*Proof (human):*`, `>` steps with `Ass` / `Have` / `Show` / `Case`. `-ai.md` copies human verbatim; extra `` **`lean_name`** `` line only when Lean ≠ id line.

